/*Write code that creates an array named odds and stores all odd numbers between -6 and 38 into it using a for loop.
Make the array's size exactly large enough to store the numbers.

array declaration format

type[] name = new type[length]; 

for each i < 22 , multiply i by 2 - 5
eg: i = 0 -> 0 * 2 - 5 = -5
eg: i = 5 -> 5 * 2 - 5 = 5

odds[i] = the value of the index position
eg: odds[0] = -5
eg: odds[1] = -3
eg: odds[21] = 37
*/



int[] odds = new int[22];
for(int i = 0; i < 22; i++) {
        odds[i] = i * 2 - 5; 
}




